    <span id="topic1" >SCOPE OF WORK & METHODOLOGY FOR PMC</span>
    <ul>
      <li >Detailed cash flow vis-a-vis  quantum of work execution and S-curve shall prepared and circulated.</li>
      <li >Detailed QA/QC plan in conjunction with specification including format development and approval of client.</li>
      <li >Material procurement plan in line with the resource requirement shall be prepared and inventory control and lead time shall be  highlighted.</li>
    <li >Detail HSSE plan shall be prepared which shall included all the health, safety, sanitation & environmental plan. These will be prepared in line with the contract  document and prevailing local conditions.</li>
    </ul>

  </div>

  <div class="mySlides fade">
    <span id="topic1">FIELD MOBILISATION</span>
    <ul>
      <li >Site Possession.</li>
      <li >Field Office Setup.</li>
      <li >Ensure the temporary works viz. office, storage, labour camp, lavatory are established as per approved drawings.</li>
    <li >Labour Licence and insurance assured.</li>
    <li>Visit to quarries for materials and its testing; Ensure materials sufficient for construction.</li>
    <li>Display of Approved material.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="mySlides fade">
    <span id="topic1">DESIGN DRAWINGS & BOQ</span>
    <ul>
      <li >Design Review as per the site conditions and modifications in consultation with Design Architect and Engineers.</li>
      <li >Topographic survey and the quantity survey for reconfirmation of the bill of quantities.</li>
      <li >Ensure that the drawings are available at least one month ahead of the execution; accordingly schedule for design drawings amended.</li>
    <li >Register of working drawings and details.</li>
    <li>Ensure that as built drawings are developed.</li>
    <li>Ensured of validation of buildings and if changes, revalidation be ensured.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>


  <div class="mySlides fade">
    <span id="topic1">SITE MANAGEMENT (GENERAL)</span>
    <ul>
      <li >Full time day to day supervision of work.</li>
      <li >Meeting with designers as and when required and recording.</li>
      <li >Ensure HSSE norms implemented at site.</li>
    <li >Log book for site orders.</li>
    <li>Record of visits by higher authorities.</li>
    <li>Co-ordination of Various line agencies including approving authority  and other statuary bodies if required.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>



  <div class="mySlides fade">
    <span id="topic1">MATERIAL PROCUREMENT & LABOR MANAGMENT</span>
    <ul>
      <li >Ensure approved materials are sufficient at site as per material procurement plan.</li>
      <li >Ensure labour forces (skilled and unskilled) and supervisors are sufficient at site.</li>
      <li >Materials Records
        <ol type="I">
          <li class="inner-inner-li" >Cement Statement ( Receipt/ Consumption/ Balance) on daily basis.</li></li>
        </ol>

    <li >Steel Register on daily basis.</li>
<li>Daily record of other construction materials.</li>
<li>Daily record of labours.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>


  <div class="mySlides fade">
    <span id="topic1">QUALITY CONTROL</span>
    <ul>
      <li >Testing of materials in field and  laboratories and approval, viz. testing of fine  & coarse aggregates, cement, reinforcement, water and any other construction materials/ fittings, fixtures deemed necessary.</li>
      <li >To ensure the workmanship in line with the design drawings before the permanent works are done viz. reinforcement work, formwork etc.</li>
      <li >Testing of workmanship in permanent works viz. concrete cubes, field density tests.</li>
    <li >Post verification on the permanent work and record defects, if any.</li>
    <li>Records
      <ol type="I">
        <li class="inner-inner-li" >Concrete Pour card approval and records.</li>
        <li class="inner-inner-li">Register for testing of cubes and results.</li>
        <li class="inner-inner-li">Test registers other materials/ fittings, fixtures.</li>
        <li class="inner-inner-li">Register of defects.</li>
      </ol>
<li>Time Control: Time is the essence of Contract.</li>
<li>Day to day monitoring of the progress of work and its evaluation compared to the Program schedule.</li>
<li>If delay on any part of the project, necessary measures to be taken for the recovery of the delay.</li>
<li>Valid Time Extensions.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>




  <div class="mySlides fade">
    <span id="topic1">REPORTING</span>
    <ul>
      <li >Daily Progress Report.</li>
      <li >Fortnightly Progress Report
        <ol type="I">
          <li class="inner-inner-li" >Progress of work (physical and financial).</li>
          <li class="inner-inner-li">Site log book.</li>
          <li class="inner-inner-li">Meetings</li>
          <li class="inner-inner-li">Correspondence</li>
          <li class="inner-inner-li" >Record of visits and instruction of higher authorities.</li>
          <li class="inner-inner-li">Decisions on additions, omission and alternations.</li>
          <li class="inner-inner-li">Material and Labour records.</li>
          <li class="inner-inner-li">Test Reports</li>
          <li class="inner-inner-li">Changes in designs/ shop drawings.</li>
          <li class="inner-inner-li">Photographs</li>
        </ol>

  </div>


